flowRoot.flowPara: GFDRR, through its Nepal DRM Country Program, has worked alongside the Government of Nepal to proactively manage disaster risks by organizing flood management projects, conducting structural surveys, and providing technical assistance for seismic-resistant modifications to buildings within Kathmandu and greater Nepal.

flowRoot.flowPara: The City of Dhaka, Bangladesh opened up its building footprints database, containing over 50,000 structures as part of larger efforts toward disaster preparedness.

To go along with its building footprints database, the city of Dhaka, Bangladesh, opened up its structural survey database, which includes building plans and photographs for many of the buildings in Dhaka. This information provides important context on the state and use of buildings in the city.
